value.value: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a disturbance in organismal or cellular homeostasis caused by a metal ion stimulus.
DNA N-glycosylase activity acting on deaminated bases.
DNA N-glycosylase activity acting on deaminated adenine (hypoxanthine).
DNA N-glycosylase activity acting on deaminated guanine (xanthine).
DNA N-glycosylase activity acting on deaminated guanine where the resulting base (oxanine) is generated by NO- or HNO2-induced nitrosative deamination.
An actin filament bundle in which the filaments are tightly packed (approximately 10-20 nm apart) and oriented with the same polarity.
A small ribonucleoprotein complex involved in formation of the spliceosome.

label.value: calcium ion transmembrane import into cytosol

value.value: A process in which a calcium ion is transported from one side of a membrane to the other into the cytosol by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

The region of a polarized cell other than its tips or ends (in some cell types, one end may be called the apex and the other the base). For example, in a polarized epithelial cell, the lateral part includes the cell sides which interface adjacent cells.
The region directly beneath the plasma membrane of the lateral portion of the cell.
Merging of two or more vacuoles, or of vacuoles and vesicles within a cell to form a single larger vacuole.

label.value: potassium ion export across plasma membrane

value.value: The directed movement of potassium ions from inside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the extracellular region.
The directed movement of L-arginine from outside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the cytosol.
The directed movement of L-lysine from outside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the cytosol.
The modification of histone H3 by addition of two methyl groups to lysine at position 36 of the histone.
Any vesicle that is part of the intracellular region.
Catalysis of the reaction: nucleoside triphosphate + RNA(n) = diphosphate + RNA(n+1); the synthesis of RNA from ribonucleotide triphosphates in the presence of a nucleic acid template.
A cellular component consisting of one leaflet of a membrane bilayer and any proteins embedded or anchored in it or attached to its surface.
The lipid bilayer that forms the outer-most layer of an organelle.

definition.value: Examples include the outer membranes of double membrane bound organelles such as mitochondria as well as the bounding membranes of single-membrane bound organelles such as lysosomes.

value.value: A membrane that is a (regional) part of the plasma membrane.

definition.value: Note that this term should not be used for direct manual annotation as it should always be possible to choose a more specific subclass.

value.value: The attachment of one cell to another cell via adhesion molecules.
The attachment of two unicellular organisms to each other.
The clustering together of unicellular organisms in suspension form aggregates.

The binding by a cell-adhesion protein on a cell surface to an adhesion molecule on another cell surface or an external substrate, to mediate adhesion of the cell to the external substrate or to another cell.
The binding by a cell-adhesion protein on the cell surface to an extracellular matrix component, to mediate adhesion of the cell to another cell.
The process by which centromeres/kinetochores become localized to clusters.

definition.value: As inner kinetochores are an integral part of centromeres, we treat centromere and kinetochore clustering as the same process.

value.value: The process in which a monoatomic cation is transported across a membrane. Monatomic cations (also called simple cations) are positively charged ions consisting of exactly one atom.
The directed movement of some substance from outside of a cell into a cell. This may occur via transport across the plasma membrane or via endocytosis.

label.value: inorganic anion import across plasma membrane

value.value: The directed movement of inorganic anions from outside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the cytosol.

label.value: inorganic cation import across plasma membrane

value.value: The directed movement of inorganic cations from outside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the cytosol.
The process in which an inorganic ion is transported across a membrane.

definition.value: Note that this term is not intended for use in annotating lateral movement within membranes.

value.value: The process in which an inorganic anion is transported across a membrane.

definition.value: Note that this term is not intended for use in annotating lateral movement within membranes.

value.value: A process in which an inorganic cation is transported from one side of a membrane to the other by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

definition.value: Note that this term is not intended for use in annotating lateral movement within membranes.

value.value: Any subdivision of a chromosome along its length.

definition.value: Chromosomal regions include parts that are not part of the chromatin. Examples include the kinetochore.

value.value: The directed movement of adenine from outside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the cytosol.

label.value: calcium ion import across plasma membrane

value.value: The directed movement of calcium ions from outside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the cytosol.
The directed movement of a carbohydrate from outside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the cytosol.

label.value: copper ion import across plasma membrane

value.value: The directed movement of copper ions from outside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the cytosol.

label.value: iron ion import across cell outer membrane

value.value: The directed movement of iron ions from outside of a cell, across the cell outer membrane and into the periplasmic space.
The directed movement of glucose from outside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the cytosol.
The directed movement of guanine from outside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the cytosol.
The directed movement of L-glutamate from outside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the cytosol.
The directed movement of leucine from outside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the cytosol.
The directed movement of malate from outside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the cytosol.

label.value: malonic acid import across plasma membrane

value.value: The directed movement of malonic acid from outside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the cytosol.

label.value: nickel cation import across plasma membrane

value.value: The directed movement of nickel cations from outside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the cytosol.
The directed movement of pantothenate from outside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the cytosol.
The directed movement of serine from outside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the cytosol.

label.value: sodium ion import across plasma membrane

value.value: The directed movement of sodium ions from outside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the cytosol.
The directed movement of succinate from outside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the cytosol.
